div.p: The site navigation utilizes arrow, enter, escape, and space bar key commands. Left and right arrows move across top level links and expand / close menus in sub levels. Up and Down arrows will open main level menus and toggle through sub tier links. Enter and space open menus and escape closes them as well. Tab will move on to the next part of the site rather than go through menu items.

Based on the guidance available to us, our confidence in having the building prepared for students as well as limiting access to the building, the administration has developed the following course of action.

Both the Governor and the State Superintendent have requested schools provide continuity of instruction so that students continue to have access to learning. During this time we will offer free daily pre-packaged lunches to all students. Students and siblings under the age of 18 will be eligible. Simply complete the link below so our staff knows how many meals to prepare for that day. Starting on Tuesday, March 17, drivers only need to pull up to the kitchen door, #10, in the EAST LOT near the student cafeteria. No one will exit their vehicle. Your pre-ordered meals will be brought to you. There will be cones and a sign to identify the food pick-up location. Walk-ups are welcome.
